<chapter id="crm">
  <title>CRM Module</title>

  <para>The <guimenu>CRM</guimenu> module organizes all of your contacts in
  one central location. This ideal setup eliminates the need for duplicate
  entries when an account has multiple classifications (i.e., a customer who
  is also a vendor) or when a contact is associated with more than one
  entity.</para>

  <para>Initially, you categorize accounts as either an organization or
  individual. Then identify the accounts as a customer or prospect, and
  further define them as a vendor, partner and/or competitor as needed.
  Additional functionality is available when various classifications are
  selected.</para>

  <para>From <guimenu>CRM</guimenu> you can manage incidents, create to-dos,
  monitor projects and track opportunities. You have the ability to create
  stand alone to-dos or associate to-dos with incidents and
  opportunities.</para>

  <para>The following topics will be covered in this chapter:<itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Universal address book</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Accounts</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Contacts</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Incident management</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>To-Do list management</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Project management</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Opportunity management</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist></para>

